      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Orange Juice Tariff Hinders Trade Pact for U.S. and Brazil'' (front page, April 24):</p>
        <p>It was interesting to learn that Brazil exports 99 percent of the orange juice it produces because ''most of the 170 million people in Brazil are not in the habit of drinking orange juice.''</p>
        <p>With a little bit of savvy the Brazilian orange juice industry could tap that huge market. It worked in the United States beginning in the 1930's.</p>
        <p>Just find a hot-shot ad agency to come up with a snappy slogan like ''Have you had your orange juice today?'' Wrap some copy around it, get pictures of attractive models drinking the stuff and advertise heavily. It may take a few years, but eventually orange juice could become the national breakfast eye-opener it has become here.</p>
        <p>And, it turns out, orange juice is good for you!</p>
        <p>GLENN  SNYDER  Mamaroneck, N.Y., April 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
